HEADWORD: Gougeshell
<hw>Gouge"shell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A sharp-edged, tubular, marine shell, of the genus
<gen>Vermetus</gen>; also, the pinna. See <er>Vermetus</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

